  "body": "unshuffleList() can represent a significant part of an epoch transition. This issue recaps some work to check it performance.\r\n\r\n1. Comparison against Lighthouse\r\n - Lighthouse [swap or not bench](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/stable/consensus/swap_or_not_shuffle/benches/benches.rs)\r\n - Lodestar [shuffle bench in a branch](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/dapplion%2Fbenchmark-shuffle/packages/beacon-state-transition/test/perf/shuffle/shuffle.perf.ts)\r\n\r\n| list size |         Lightouse | Lodestar\r\n| --- | --- | --- |\r\n| 512     | 254.04 us | 1.6034 ms (x6)\r\n| 16384  |  6.2046 ms | 18.272 ms (x3)\r\n| 4000000 | 1.5617 s  | 4.9690 s  (x3)\r\n\r\n2. Cost of hashing in shuffle\r\n\r\nChanging the hash function with an echo function, estimate the total time spent hashing which is around 80%. Our hashing function could be optimized with native bindings, with a ~1.5-2x improve. With that unshuffleList() cpu time could be reduced by 40%.\r\n\r\n3. Profile for the record\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-04-09 11-37-37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/114164063-2a76bc00-992b-11eb-8f67-57f0ed8bb756.png)\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-04-09 11-37-53](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/114164080-2ea2d980-992b-11eb-80b1-4b474204b57a.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
